3
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:37,280
(Episode 23)

4
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:44,000
Thank you for staying by my side.

5
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:51,040
Do you think it's worth it?

6
00:01:58,599 --> 00:02:00,560
I feel like this is a path I must go through in my life.

7
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:02,519
I have to walk this path...

8
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:04,280
to meet the people I must meet.

9
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:05,840
Looking at this the other way around,

10
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:07,319
if you want to meet the people you must meet,

11
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:10,240
you must walk an inevitable path.

12
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:12,159
I told you before.

13
00:02:12,159 --> 00:02:13,199
Even if I just stay at home,

14
00:02:13,530 --> 00:02:16,120
I can relax for the rest of my life.

15
00:02:17,159 --> 00:02:18,159
But I don't want that.

16
00:02:18,810 --> 00:02:21,000
I want to have more experience.

17
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:22,370
I want to explore out here as much as I can.

18
00:02:22,919 --> 00:02:26,370
I want to enrich myself...

19
00:02:26,479 --> 00:02:27,530
and become an interesting person.

20
00:02:27,530 --> 00:02:28,680
I want more people to like me.

21
00:02:34,199 --> 00:02:37,199
I originally came to persuade you.

22
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:42,280
Because this was my fault after all.

23
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:44,800
But I've changed my mind.

24
00:02:46,439 --> 00:02:47,680
You're right.

25
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:49,280
You have to walk an inevitable path...

26
00:02:49,520 --> 00:02:51,599
to meet the people you must meet.

27
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:54,080
It's good to experience it.

28
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:58,000
Okay.

29
00:03:04,639 --> 00:03:06,280
Have you ever seen a shooting star as a child?

30
00:03:06,479 --> 00:03:07,479
Yes.

31
00:03:07,599 --> 00:03:08,680
I've never seen one before.

32
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:10,520
Then your life...

33
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,360
isn't very plentiful either.

34
00:03:14,599 --> 00:03:16,319
We might be able to see one today.

35
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:22,599
- What? - It's a reflection on the glass.

36
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:26,159
You're so annoying.

37
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:43,280
Pull over right here.

38
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:44,680
Don't go any further.

39
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:02,159
Shengda suddenly raised the price of the precast slabs...

40
00:04:02,159 --> 00:04:03,280
by eight percent.

41
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:04,960
They claim it's because the market isn't doing well right now.

42
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:06,560
This puts us in a very passive position.

43
00:04:08,599 --> 00:04:12,039
We quoted our prices to the client based on the buying price.

44
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:14,120
If he raises the price by eight percent,

45
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:16,680
then we'll have to bear the losses.

46
00:04:17,170 --> 00:04:18,759
I said everything I could,

47
00:04:18,759 --> 00:04:20,279
but they wouldn't budge.

48
00:04:20,639 --> 00:04:22,240
They said it was their boss's orders.

49
00:04:22,610 --> 00:04:23,680
Mr. Hou.

50
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:25,959
It's hard for people of our rank to solve this problem.

51
00:04:26,610 --> 00:04:27,680
Okay, I got it.

52
00:04:28,399 --> 00:04:29,959
- You may go. - Okay.

53
00:04:35,079 --> 00:04:36,839
It looks like...

54
00:04:36,839 --> 00:04:39,079
Mr. Sheng doesn't consider us as a friend anymore.

55
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:41,439
He reacted quite quickly.

56
00:04:42,759 --> 00:04:44,879
He sure went all out to teach me a lesson.

57
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:47,800
Mr. Hou Junior.

58
00:04:48,610 --> 00:04:52,240
All my car keys and bank cards are here.

59
00:04:52,879 --> 00:04:54,079
Help me give them to Mr. Hou.

60
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:56,199
Now, I'm going to my office...

61
00:04:56,199 --> 00:04:58,279
to make a copy of my personal files.

62
00:04:59,079 --> 00:05:00,079
That's okay, right?

63
00:05:01,199 --> 00:05:02,199
Yes.

64
00:05:12,079 --> 00:05:13,079
Come in.

65
00:05:16,730 --> 00:05:17,730
Mr. Hou.

66
00:05:17,730 --> 00:05:19,610
Mr. Hou Junior told me to give this to you.

67
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:22,480
You may leave.

68
00:05:42,199 --> 00:05:43,439
What is Mr. Hou Junior...

69
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:46,399
That brat.

70
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:49,040
He's actually being serious.

71
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:01,319
He gave up everything...

72
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:03,040
and declared independence from me.

73
00:06:05,279 --> 00:06:06,639
You love him so much.

74
00:06:06,959 --> 00:06:08,920
The company is in such tough times right now,

75
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:09,959
yet he's doing this.

76
00:06:10,279 --> 00:06:11,720
That's just wrong.

77
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:12,879
Just let him go.

78
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,600
He'd better go as far as he can.

79
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:17,160
Out of sight, out of mind.

80
00:06:19,839 --> 00:06:21,000
Just let him go.

81
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:25,600
He's still a kid.

82
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:27,319
He's being immature for doing this.

83
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:30,879
You must not take this to heart...

84
00:06:31,079 --> 00:06:32,680
and harm your own health.

85
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:34,240
It's not worth it.

86
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:36,040
If he were still young,

87
00:06:37,439 --> 00:06:39,240
I could say he didn't know any better.

88
00:06:40,279 --> 00:06:41,720
I could forgive him.

89
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:45,279
But he's all grown up now.

90
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:50,079
There's no way I'll forgive him.

91
00:06:56,959 --> 00:06:58,439
Don't say that.

92
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:01,519
A father and son can't be at odds forever.

93
00:07:01,959 --> 00:07:03,879
He'll come around one day.

94
00:07:04,759 --> 00:07:05,759
Besides,

95
00:07:06,199 --> 00:07:07,800
exploring out there is good for him too.

96
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:08,800
He should suffer a bit more.

97
00:07:09,879 --> 00:07:11,399
Then he'll become more mature.

98
00:07:13,759 --> 00:07:17,160
He has no idea how difficult the world out there is.

99
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:22,360
It looks like he won't turn back until he hits a dead end.

100
00:07:23,120 --> 00:07:24,959
He's hopeless.

101
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:29,519
He has always been rebellious.

102
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:33,360
He insists on showing me that he can handle things alone.

103
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:40,000
I'm really worried about him.

104
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:44,439
Ma Yong.

105
00:07:46,199 --> 00:07:49,279
We've been through so many obstacles and challenges...

106
00:07:49,279 --> 00:07:50,680
throughout all these years.

107
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:54,360
We've experienced failure and betrayal.

108
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:56,040
Although our enemies were everywhere,

109
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:59,160
we were never alone.

110
00:08:02,319 --> 00:08:03,319
Thank you.

111
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:06,240
Thank goodness you're here.

112
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:09,279
I feel a lot more relieved.

113
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:16,399
Why don't you have some water?

114
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:18,639
It's okay. You can get back to work.

115
00:08:18,639 --> 00:08:20,120
I want to be alone for a bit.

116
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:45,279
Is there anything else you need to take?

117
00:08:46,759 --> 00:08:48,639
No. I'm not taking anything else.

118
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:56,960
This is all I need.

119
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:58,600
Come on.

120
00:09:18,559 --> 00:09:20,600
I never realized how tall this building was.

121
00:09:22,210 --> 00:09:24,399
You know, my dad's business is doing well.

122
00:09:24,399 --> 00:09:26,559
I just muddle along like a nobody every day...

123
00:09:26,559 --> 00:09:27,679
and I keep going against him.

124
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:28,919
It's quite fun, isn't it?

125
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:31,600
Apologize to your dad...

126
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:32,919
and tell him that you've thought it through.

127
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:35,759
You can just work seriously from now on.

128
00:09:35,759 --> 00:09:36,879
That's impossible.

129
00:09:37,159 --> 00:09:38,519
If I'm alone,

130
00:09:38,519 --> 00:09:41,720
I can live however I want whether it's good or bad.

131
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:42,720
Isn't that right?

132
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:49,559
Why is smoke coming out of this bike?

133
00:09:52,210 --> 00:09:53,210
Watch out!

134
00:09:57,210 --> 00:09:59,210
- Be careful. Run! - Run!

135
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:02,720
Run!

136
00:10:03,759 --> 00:10:05,159
Why did you jump on me again?

137
00:10:06,210 --> 00:10:07,210
Get up.

138
00:10:08,279 --> 00:10:09,279
Get up.

139
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:11,360
Shi Yi.

140
00:10:12,210 --> 00:10:13,210
Shi Yi.

141
00:10:14,330 --> 00:10:15,330
Shi Yi.

142
00:10:15,879 --> 00:10:16,879
Shi Yi.

143
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:19,600
- What's going on? - What happened?

144
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,159
What happened?

145
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:27,210
What happened?

146
00:10:27,210 --> 00:10:29,120
I have no idea, Mr. Ma. There's smoke and fire.

147
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:30,210
Hurry and take a look.

148
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:32,120
There's a fire down there.

149
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:40,840
Is this the Security Department?

150
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:41,879
I'm Ma Yong.

151
00:10:42,159 --> 00:10:43,519
What's going on downstairs?

152
00:10:46,210 --> 00:10:47,210
What?

153
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:56,120
- What's going on? - What's happening?

154
00:10:56,840 --> 00:10:57,840
Is there a fire?

155
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:01,360
- Where's the fire? - What's going on?

156
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:02,519
There's a fire!

157
00:11:04,039 --> 00:11:05,039
No way.

158
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:09,320
Something has happened.

159
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:10,360
Mr. Hou, there's trouble.

160
00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:12,039
What happened?

161
00:11:12,039 --> 00:11:13,240
You're in such a panic.

162
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:15,960
There was an explosion downstairs.

163
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:17,480
It happened right next to Hou Jue's car.

164
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:20,399
Where's Hou Jue now?

165
00:11:20,639 --> 00:11:21,639
Where is he?

166
00:11:21,639 --> 00:11:22,639
Hou Jue is at the scene of the accident.

167
00:11:22,639 --> 00:11:23,919
But his situation is unknown.

168
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:26,679
Who is trying to harm him?

169
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:33,559
No. I need to go and have a look.

170
00:11:33,679 --> 00:11:34,679
Are you sure?

171
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:35,919
I'm going to have a look.

172
00:11:36,159 --> 00:11:37,159
Mr. Hou.

173
00:11:37,279 --> 00:11:38,559
- All right. - What's wrong?

174
00:11:38,759 --> 00:11:40,200
Hou Jue is fine.

175
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,279
Are you sure?

176
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:43,120
He's safe and sound.

177
00:11:43,360 --> 00:11:45,360
But Wu Shi Yi got injured from protecting him.

178
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:46,919
She's already in the hospital.

179
00:11:49,759 --> 00:11:50,799
Are you okay?

180
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:52,440
Thank goodness he has a bodyguard.

181
00:11:53,799 --> 00:11:55,360
Thank goodness for Wu Shi Yi.

182
00:11:55,919 --> 00:11:57,039
That scared me.

183
00:11:57,440 --> 00:11:59,159
Good thing Shi Yi was there.

184
00:12:00,279 --> 00:12:01,960
Otherwise, Hou Jue would have been doomed.

185
00:12:04,519 --> 00:12:06,080
That scared me to death.

186
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:08,440
- Gosh, my heart. - Are you okay?

187
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,240
Take it slow.

188
00:12:21,159 --> 00:12:22,279
Slowly.

189
00:12:23,360 --> 00:12:26,279
Go to the scene right now and check the situation.

190
00:12:26,279 --> 00:12:27,600
- Don't mind me. Go on. - Okay.

191
00:12:27,960 --> 00:12:30,360
- Hurry. - Don't worry. Calm down.

192
00:12:38,519 --> 00:12:39,519
Officer.

193
00:12:39,919 --> 00:12:43,240
How is the investigation going?

194
00:12:43,240 --> 00:12:44,559
Things should be fine now.

195
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:47,000
We won't know until we get the results of the investigation.

196
00:12:58,639 --> 00:13:00,759
Doctor, how is she?

197
00:13:00,759 --> 00:13:02,320
She has been stitched up. The patient is conscious.

198
00:13:02,519 --> 00:13:04,080
- Did she get stitches? - Yes.

199
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:06,840
- How many stitches did she get? - Ten stitches.

200
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:09,200
She suffered a wound on her left rib.

201
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:12,360
Is there anything else we need to be careful of?

202
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:14,440
She has to come back on time to get her dressing changed.

203
00:13:14,919 --> 00:13:16,960
Is her injury serious?

204
00:13:16,960 --> 00:13:19,080
It's not that serious.

205
00:13:19,279 --> 00:13:20,279
It's just a superficial wound.

206
00:13:20,279 --> 00:13:21,320
Her internal organs are unharmed.

207
00:13:21,559 --> 00:13:22,559
All right, doctor.

208
00:13:22,559 --> 00:13:23,639
Thank you.

209
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:27,240
Mr. Hou.

210
00:13:28,279 --> 00:13:30,279
Please come with us to the station to assist the investigation.

211
00:13:30,840 --> 00:13:33,360
Can you let me take a look at her after she comes out first?

212
00:13:34,639 --> 00:13:36,159
Mr. Hou, don't worry.

213
00:13:36,159 --> 00:13:37,159
We're here.

214
00:13:37,559 --> 00:13:39,080
Go with the police.

215
00:13:40,440 --> 00:13:41,440
- Okay. - Let's go.

216
00:13:41,799 --> 00:13:43,240
- Look after her. - Okay.

217
00:13:43,240 --> 00:13:44,440
- Look after her. - I'm here.

218
00:13:45,559 --> 00:13:46,559
Don't worry.

219
00:13:50,759 --> 00:13:52,720
Zhou Quan, go with them.

220
00:13:52,720 --> 00:13:54,240
- Take care of Mr. Hou. - Okay.

221
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:58,039
- Be careful. - Don't worry.

222
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:10,600
How are you feeling?

223
00:14:10,799 --> 00:14:12,279
I'm fine. It's just a minor injury.

224
00:14:13,559 --> 00:14:14,559
Shi Yi.

225
00:14:14,559 --> 00:14:15,559
Where's Hou Jue?

226
00:14:15,559 --> 00:14:16,559
Is he okay?

227
00:14:16,559 --> 00:14:17,799
He's fine.

228
00:14:17,799 --> 00:14:19,039
He stayed with you the whole time.

229
00:14:19,320 --> 00:14:21,559
The police just took him away to help with the investigation.

230
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:24,600
I'm glad he's okay.

231
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:26,360
Shi Yi, don't worry.

232
00:14:26,360 --> 00:14:27,919
I've already asked Zhou Quan to replace you...

233
00:14:27,919 --> 00:14:30,039
and protect Mr. Hou around the clock.

234
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:32,320
Just focus on getting better.

235
00:14:33,279 --> 00:14:35,080
It's really just a small injury.

236
00:14:35,360 --> 00:14:37,039
It's true. I'll be fine in a couple of days.

237
00:14:37,159 --> 00:14:38,200
This is our discipline.

238
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:40,720
It's not just for your health,

239
00:14:40,720 --> 00:14:42,679
but it's also for the safety of our clients.

240
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:44,240
Excuse me.

241
00:14:44,240 --> 00:14:46,080
We need to take the patient to the observation room first.

242
00:14:46,080 --> 00:14:47,080
- I'm sorry. - I'm sorry.

243
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:48,120
It's okay.

244
00:14:49,759 --> 00:14:50,759
